                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1226">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2905.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-26T21:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 26, 1912—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Relative to the Ciudad Juárez situation and according to the information conveyed
                    in my February 26, 5 p.m., I have sent a friendly but firm note to Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
